1
00:00:00,875 --> 00:00:02,001
[JAO] Can you do me a favor?

2
00:00:02,043 --> 00:00:02,836
Can you…

3
00:00:02,837 --> 00:00:04,253
give this to Allie?

4
00:00:04,254 --> 00:00:07,215
Please tell her she can sell that to start over.

5
00:00:07,257 --> 00:00:08,716
Don't you want to stay

6
00:00:08,717 --> 00:00:11,177
and experience the better version of the curse?

7
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:12,387
Have you seen Jao?

8
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,096
Kara, you should go.

9
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:15,472
Find where Jao is.

10
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:17,475
[JAO] Mom. Dad.

11
00:00:17,517 --> 00:00:19,143
I’m sorry…

12
00:00:19,144 --> 00:00:20,437
[SIARGAONON] it took me so long to go home.

13
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:21,688
Your son’s home.

14
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:23,272
We’re not poor anymore.

15
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:24,274
[KARA] You’re from here?

16
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:26,359
[JAO] I was born here.

17
00:00:26,443 --> 00:00:29,361
- Wow! -Freshly-made kinilaw a la Carol.

18
00:00:29,362 --> 00:00:30,780
[HAN BIN] Let me try!

19
00:00:30,822 --> 00:00:32,198
This is so delicious!

20
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:32,866
[PEARL COUGHS] Wait.

21
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:33,700
- Too spicy! - Wait. Are you okay?

22
00:00:33,742 --> 00:00:34,825
I’ll give you milk!

23
00:00:34,826 --> 00:00:36,285
You're the only Siargaonon I know

24
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:38,371
who can’t handle spicy food.

25
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:39,080
[PEARL GROANS]

26
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:40,373
[JAO] Nothing has changed.

27
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:43,251
Our old house

28
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:44,919
was about a five minute walk.

29
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:47,547
Everything you see here?

30
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:49,007
I grew up around all of it.

31
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:50,883
I hated being poor here, Kara.

32
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:53,094
Poverty took my parents away from me.

33
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:56,139
[KARA] I believe everything happened

34
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:57,474
for a reason.

35
00:00:57,515 --> 00:00:59,517
And I'm glad you’ve come so far, Jao.

36
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:03,563
[KARA] So it’s your birthday.

37
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:05,648
Aren’t you going to celebrate?

38
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:07,650
[JAO LAUGHS]

39
00:01:08,109 --> 00:01:10,111
I don’t usually...

40
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:12,738
celebrate my birthday.

41
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:13,740
But…

42
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:17,160
my mom and I would always do something

43
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,870
together on our birthday.

44
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:36,679
[JAO] This is it.

45
00:01:37,388 --> 00:01:39,724
This is how I want to celebrate my birthday.

46
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,769
Lounging on the sand…

47
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:46,647
listening to the waves, and...

48
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,358
staring up at the clouds.

49
00:01:49,275 --> 00:01:50,276
Simple.

50
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:54,531
I get it.

51
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,286
[KARA] Good thing I baked a cake.

52
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:02,413
You shouldn’t have.

53
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:04,541
Happy birthday, Jao!

54
00:02:04,749 --> 00:02:05,750
Make a wish.

55
00:02:06,042 --> 00:02:07,252
[KARA] Make it a good one.

56
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:08,711
You deserve it.

57
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:18,429
[JAO BLOWS]

58
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:26,354
Happy birthday to your mom, too.

59
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:28,690
Look.

60
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:31,568
There's pancit in the sky!

61
00:02:31,609 --> 00:02:33,610
Huh? Pancit?

62
00:02:33,611 --> 00:02:34,987
- [JAO] Looks more like spaghetti! - [KARA] No, look!

63
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:36,322
[KARA] It's pancit!

64
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:38,866
What’s that coming in?

65
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:39,784
It looks like…

66
00:02:40,785 --> 00:02:42,745
Looks like a fondue pot.

67
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:45,039
[KARA AND JAO LAUGH]

68
00:02:45,081 --> 00:02:45,999
[KARA] A fondue pot?

69
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,332
[KARA AND JAO LAUGH]

70
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:49,502
Go on, make a wish for your mom.

71
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:56,718
Actually,

72
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,470
I know what my mom would wish for.

73
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:02,056
What?

74
00:03:03,182 --> 00:03:04,392
[JAO] Kara, come on!

75
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:13,151
[ALON BY JL]

76
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:30,144
Do you see that?

77
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:32,021
The boat?

78
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:34,357
[JAO] Around here,

79
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:38,277
if you own a boat that big, it means you’re pretty well-off.

80
00:04:39,487 --> 00:04:41,489
When my mom was still alive,

81
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,742
she always dreamed of buying a boat just like that

82
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,536
if we ever had the money.

83
00:04:46,577 --> 00:04:48,663
We’d catch more fish

84
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:49,789
and earn more money.

85
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:53,166
I used to want a boat with a TV.

86
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,836
Because once you're out at sea,

87
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:55,962
it gets pretty boring.

88
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:57,213
A TV?

89
00:04:58,006 --> 00:04:59,007
Why not?

90
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,134
Okay.

91
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,636
Hey! Where are you going?

92
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:05,179
[JAO] I’m swimming over there.

93
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:06,556
I’m buying that boat.

94
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:08,433
Can you make it?

95
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:16,607
Of course I can.

96
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:19,068
I’m Jao from Siargao.

97
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:21,112
See that ocean?

98
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,656
That’s my playground.

99
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,493
I’m from Siargao!

100
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,287
Can you swim that far?

101
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:30,371
You bet!

102
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:31,414
Come on!

103
00:05:58,399 --> 00:05:59,275
[KOREAN] Aigoo! Gosh!

104
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:01,318
[KOREAN] Ireon geol yeogi wae beorineun geoya? Why would you throw something like this here?

105
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:02,320
[KOREAN] Jeongmal. Seriously.

106
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:05,531
[KOREAN] Aigoo! Gosh!

107
00:06:09,577 --> 00:06:10,578
[HAN BIN GRUNTS]

108
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:13,956
Let me help you out, brother.

109
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:15,541
Thank you, man!

110
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,089
By the way,

111
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,508
can I ask you a question?

112
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:24,717
Yes!

113
00:06:26,636 --> 00:06:28,054
Do you like Pearl?

114
00:06:30,515 --> 00:06:31,516
No.

115
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,726
Are you sure?

116
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:38,064
Why do you ask?

117
00:06:39,899 --> 00:06:41,400
Because I like Pearl.

118
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:43,027
Oh.

119
00:06:44,737 --> 00:06:47,740
I mean, I really like her and I’d like to get to know her more.

120
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:50,159
But if you also like her,

121
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:51,786
I respect that.

122
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:53,495
No, no!

123
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:54,997
Pearl works for me.

124
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:56,414
I mean,

125
00:06:56,415 --> 00:06:58,835
I don’t want her to feel awkward at work.

126
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,211
Okay.

127
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,005
Well, the reason I asked is because...

128
00:07:03,047 --> 00:07:05,049
I respect you, too, brother.

129
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:07,385
You’re like a brother to me on this island.

130
00:07:07,426 --> 00:07:09,428
[HAN BIN CHUCKLES] Thanks, bro!

131
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,097
So…

132
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:13,891
is it okay if I court Pearl?

133
00:07:16,644 --> 00:07:18,020
It’s up to you, brother.

134
00:07:18,437 --> 00:07:20,648
And of course, it’s up to Pearl.

135
00:07:23,651 --> 00:07:25,361
[KOREAN] Aigoo! Gosh!

136
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:42,044
[JAO] We were so cocky back there.

137
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,796
[KARA] It was your idea.

138
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:47,216
I really can do it. You just stopped me.

139
00:07:47,758 --> 00:07:50,093
Knowing when to back off

140
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:52,388
is part of being strong, too.

141
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:57,393
There goes Ms. Kara with her words of wisdom.

142
00:07:57,435 --> 00:07:58,436
[KARA CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

143
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:04,525
Excuse me!

144
00:08:05,401 --> 00:08:07,819
Were you on that boat earlier?

145
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:08,654
Yes, sir!

146
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:11,365
Can I ask...

147
00:08:11,782 --> 00:08:13,783
how much a boat like that costs?

148
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:15,203
I’m not sure, sir.

149
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:17,246
My sister in Saudi gave it to me.

150
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:20,041
Then where did she get it?

151
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:24,419
[BOATMAN] I know a boat-builder in Pacifico.

152
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:26,964
- I can introduce you. - Okay. Thanks.

153
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:30,092
- How long would it take? - Maybe a few months.

154
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:34,180
- [JAO] Okay. - Thank you!

155
00:08:34,181 --> 00:08:35,973
- [JAO] Thank you. Bye. - [BOATMAN] Thank you.

156
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:38,601
[KARA] It's okay.

157
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:39,644
One step at a time.

158
00:08:40,269 --> 00:08:43,481
I'm sure your mom’s happy that you’re home for her birthday.

159
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:46,609
I hope so.

160
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:50,696
So if you're from here,

161
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:53,407
you must know how to surf?

162
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:56,577
I used to.

163
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:58,663
I’m not so sure anymore. I’m…

164
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,249
I'm probably a little rusty.

165
00:09:01,582 --> 00:09:03,084
Longboard or shortboard?

166
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:05,378
Longboard?

167
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:07,505
- Really? - Anyway, it’s fine!

168
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:08,839
This is enough for me.

169
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:10,466
Didn't you say one step at a time?

170
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:16,097
I’m glad I went back here because…

171
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:18,307
when I was in Manila,

172
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:21,519
I kept dreaming about this place.

173
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:23,312
Like...

174
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:25,356
it kept calling me back.

175
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,197
Mom…

176
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:34,365
Dad...

177
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:38,911
[SIARGAONON] I'm back at our beach.

178
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:45,001
You seem like a different person.

179
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:48,254
[JAO SIGHS]

180
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:50,130
If...

181
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:53,134
you see me differently now because you pity me,

182
00:09:54,051 --> 00:09:55,051
don’t.

183
00:09:55,052 --> 00:09:56,345
I’m okay.

184
00:09:57,054 --> 00:10:00,224
Are you okay that things ended with Allie?

185
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:03,019
Or are you okay with how your life’s going now?

186
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:09,483
“Boat.”

187
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:11,444
Boat.

188
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:12,737
[JAO] I’m okay with both.

189
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:15,155
[KARA] You’ve finally lost it.

190
00:10:15,156 --> 00:10:21,329
[JAO LAUGHS]

191
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:33,257
[HAN BIN VOICEOVER] Why did I lie?

192
00:10:34,383 --> 00:10:37,345
It only left a bitter taste in my mouth.

193
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:40,306
[HAN BIN SIGHS]

194
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:52,985
[HAN BIN SIGHS]

195
00:10:58,949 --> 00:10:59,950
[HAN BIN SIGHS]

196
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:08,959
[HAN BIN HUFFS]

197
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:13,714
[HAN BIN LETS OUT DEEP BREATH]

198
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,677
It’s up to Pearl,

199
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:20,012
not you.

200
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:32,066
[JAO] Did I really leave a bad first impression on you?

201
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:36,112
[KARA] I just related to Allie.

202
00:11:36,153 --> 00:11:37,154
Sorry.

203
00:11:37,738 --> 00:11:39,740
But it all makes sense now.

204
00:11:42,159 --> 00:11:43,244
[JAO] No offense taken.

205
00:11:44,453 --> 00:11:45,746
Maybe...

206
00:11:46,997 --> 00:11:48,999
I deserved it, one way or another.

207
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:52,002
But it’s funny, isn’t it?

208
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:54,922
We could have been friends from the start.

209
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,256
You were just so rude.

210
00:11:56,257 --> 00:11:57,258
Wow.

211
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:01,887
Allie and I broke up,

212
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,766
but Siargao and I reconciled.

213
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:09,228
Life’s funny like that, isn’t it?

214
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:11,188
I’ve got to hand it to you.

215
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:14,442
If that were me, I’d be completely crushed.

216
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:17,945
Uh...

217
00:12:19,029 --> 00:12:20,406
I know I’ve...

218
00:12:20,781 --> 00:12:22,575
just gotten to know you.

219
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:24,827
But if I may say…

220
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,204
I don't think you're

221
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:29,874
that kind of a person.

222
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:34,587
I feel like whenever life throws something at you,

223
00:12:35,796 --> 00:12:39,091
you’ll treat it like the waves.

224
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:41,427
- You just ride it out. - [KARA CHUCKLES]

225
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:42,720
I wish.

226
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:48,058
So, which brings me to my question.

227
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:52,980
How’d you end up in Siargao?

228
00:12:53,355 --> 00:12:54,774
[KARA CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

229
00:12:57,151 --> 00:12:58,527
I was running away.

230
00:13:00,237 --> 00:13:01,739
Running away from...

231
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:03,657
I would assume...

232
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:06,702
who or what?

233
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:08,454
My old life.

234
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:10,164
It was a mess.

235
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:13,626
You know, I'm not as strong as you think, Jao.

236
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:17,421
My toxic trait is running away from my problems.

237
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:21,258
You...

238
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:23,594
ran away from

239
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:25,387
Manila to come to Siargao.

240
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:26,847
- And I… - [KARA CHUCKLES]

241
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:28,891
ran away from Siargao

242
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:32,603
to Manila. We switched places.

243
00:13:37,441 --> 00:13:38,651
-So what was it? Come on. -[KARA CLICKS TONGUE]

244
00:13:38,692 --> 00:13:39,692
Uh...

245
00:13:39,693 --> 00:13:42,111
It’s your turn! I’ve told you so much already.

246
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:43,614
All right...

247
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:46,075
Let me guess. Ex-boyfriend?

248
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:48,535
Ex-fiancé?

249
00:13:48,536 --> 00:13:50,203
Did he cheat on you? Or maybe—

250
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:51,705
Hey, I'm not a cheater, okay?

251
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,082
Anyway,

252
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,501
I’ll tell you next time.

253
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:58,003
But you’re leaving soon, aren’t you?

254
00:13:58,045 --> 00:13:59,213
[PHONE CHIMES]

255
00:14:02,049 --> 00:14:03,050
Right on cue.

256
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,177
My secretary’s reminding me.

257
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:08,806
Back to reality.

258
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:12,643
That’s too bad. You just got home.

259
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:15,980
I thought you’d never leave this place anymore.

260
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:19,358
Well,

261
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:22,903
my life’s in Manila now.

262
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:27,074
My life is where I want it to be.

263
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:08,741
Hey, I got it.

264
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:09,825
Here.

265
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:10,826
[KARA] It's okay.

266
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:12,994
So you'll give Katig five stars.

267
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:13,996
[KARA LAUGHS]

268
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:21,420
So…?

269
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:23,297
- All right. Uh… - All right.

270
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:29,595
Thank you for everything, Kara.

271
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:32,389
[SIARGAONON] You're welcome, Jao.

272
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:35,893
Nice meeting you.

273
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:38,187
Nice knowing you, too.

274
00:15:50,574 --> 00:15:53,577
[KARA WHISPERS] Don’t look back.

275
00:15:58,832 --> 00:15:59,833
Jao!

276
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,047
What?

277
00:16:23,607 --> 00:16:25,317
[KARA WHISPERS] Please stay.

278
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:49,549
[KARA] I just wanted to tell you,

279
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:51,217
that wherever life takes you,

280
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:52,593
never forget

281
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:53,845
you’re a Siargaonon.

282
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:56,056
[PEARL] What’s the occasion? Is it your birthday, Quinito?

283
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:57,557
[HAN BIN] No, it's not his birthday.

284
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:59,351
But today, we will celebrate.

285
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:00,477
It’s my monthsary on the island.

286
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:02,104
[QUINITO] Pearl, can we talk?

287
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:04,523
I’ve been meaning to tell you this, just so we’re clear.

288
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:06,942
You’re hungover, aren’t you?

289
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:07,985
[PEARL LAUGHS]

290
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:09,778
Han Bin oppa, look.

291
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:12,197
If you don't mind, you can edit me out of the video.

292
00:17:12,239 --> 00:17:14,031
I think you're hiding something from us.

293
00:17:14,032 --> 00:17:15,158
What are you talking about?

294
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:16,576
I'm just a private person.

295
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:17,786
Is this men's clothing?

296
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:19,328
Who’s it for?

297
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:21,540
No one. I just wanted to try something new.

298
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:22,582
[KARA] What’s so funny?

299
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:23,584
[CAROL GIGGLES]

300
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:26,003
[CAROL] Nothing! I’m just happy!

301
00:17:26,044 --> 00:17:27,962
How thrilling!

302
00:17:27,963 --> 00:17:29,965
[KARA] You’re impossible, Carol!
